<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="S" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Stride2" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Stride,</orth> vb. (cf. <emph>Bestride</emph>) 1) to step over: <cit><quote>a debtor, that not dares to s. a limit,</quote> <bibl n="shak. cym 3.3.35" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. III, 3, 35</bibl></cit>.<lb />2) to mount as a rider: <cit><quote>I mean to s. your steed,</quote> <bibl n="shak. cor 1.9.71" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. I, 9, 71</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>--ing the blast,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mac 1.7.22" default="NO" valid="yes">Mcb. I, 7, 22</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>